===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

[[File:A lindworm.jpg|thumb]]

# {{lb|en|Mythology}} A lindworm is a slithering wingless type of "dragon" with scaled skin, a long serpentine body like in Chinese dragons, two clawed arms in the upper body and a dragon-like head. May have either a poisonous or fiery breath. This type of dragon is especially found in Norse mythology.
# {{lb|en|folklore and mythology}} A vague draconic creature, especially in heraldry can be just as anything a dragon can be depicted, mainly found in folklore and mythology of Germany, Scandinavia and England.

